  "original_title": "\u0b93\u0bb0\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd  \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Oranga actor arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Vazaichenai police said that an air force soldier who returned home for vacation, kidnapped himself and tied his hands, feet and mouth in the forest.",
        "The police on duty found a man in his underwear tied to a tree near a brick wadi about 500 meters from Rithithennai police check post.",
        "They also found a banner on the tree with the words, \"This is how mercenaries who help rogue politics are killed.\" After that, they rescued him and immediately admitted him to Aadar Hospital",
        "After that, the police interrogated the airman. It was revealed that he was 30-year-old Rathanasooriya Mutiansalawe from Valappanai area who was serving at Batticaloa Air Force base.",
        "He went home for vacation and reached Mahianganai yesterday (28). From there he traveled by bus to Polonnaruwa and reached Chevinapitti Batticaloa junction in the evening.",
        "From there I was chatting with my wife on my mobile phone while waiting to go to Batticaloa. However, he testified that a stranger who came from behind in a private vehicle hit him on the head and covered his face.",
        "He has testified that they were loaded in a vehicle, brought to this place after a journey of about 2 hours, took off their clothes, tied them up and left the banner and escaped.",
        "However, knowing that there were no injuries on the airman's body, the police conducted further investigations.",
        "In the investigation, he said that he had lost a lot of money in a game on his mobile phone and had borrowed money from his fellow soldiers in the camp and became a debtor after losing it in that game as well.",
        "However, he admitted to the police that he acted this way to escape from the creditor. The police informed that he was arrested after that and said that they are taking up further investigations."
      ],
